msgid ""
"If the prebuilt path doesn't exist on disk at compile time, Perry falls back "
"to `cargo build --release`."
msgstr "如果编译时磁盘上不存在该预编译路径，Perry 会回退到运行 `cargo build --release`。"

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:249
msgid "6. Update over time"
msgstr "6. 长期更新"

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:251
msgid ""
"**A new perry-ffi feature lands**: bump your `Cargo.toml`'s `perry-ffi` "
"version, rebuild prebuilts, tag a new release. Users `bun update` to pick it "
"up. Perry's manifest spec stays at v1 unless the schema changes."
msgstr "**有新的 perry-ffi 特性发布**：在你的 `Cargo.toml` 中提升 `perry-ffi` 版本，重新构建预编译产物，打一个新 release。用户通过 `bun update` 即可拿到。除非 schema 变化，否则 Perry 的 manifest 规范保持在 v1。"

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:255
msgid ""
"**A new Perry minor**: same — `perry-ffi`'s semver moves with Perry's minor. "
"The git-URL consumption (v0.5.x) means rebuilding against `main` picks it up "
"automatically."
msgstr "**Perry 发布新的 minor**：处理方式相同 —— `perry-ffi` 的 semver 跟随 Perry 的 minor 一起前进。在 v0.5.x 周期内通过 git URL 引用，意味着对 `main` 重新构建会自动获取更新。"

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:258
msgid ""
"**Breaking change to the `js_*` surface you exported**: bump your package's "
"major version (`1.0.0` → `2.0.0`). Users who pin a major aren't affected."
msgstr "**你导出的 `js_*` 表面发生破坏性变更**：提升你自己包的主版本号（`1.0.0` → `2.0.0`）。固定主版本的用户不会受影响。"

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:262
msgid "Common patterns"
msgstr "常见模式"

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:264
msgid "Async one-shot (HTTP request, DB query)"
msgstr "异步一次性调用（HTTP 请求、数据库查询）"

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:281
msgid "\"fetch: {}\""
msgstr "\"fetch: {}\""

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:288
msgid "Sync handle-based class"
msgstr "基于 handle 的同步类"

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:306
msgid "Event listeners (`.on(event, cb)`)"
msgstr "事件监听器（`.on(event, cb)`）"

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:315
msgid "// closure pointers, kept alive by the GC scanner below\n"
msgstr ""
"// closure pointers, kept alive by the GC scanner below\n"

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:358
msgid ""
"The GC scanner is **load-bearing**: without it, a malloc-triggered GC "
"between `.on(cb)` and `.emit()` will sweep the closure and the next emit "
"calls freed memory. Always register a scanner if your handles store closure "
"pointers."
msgstr "GC 扫描器是**关键所在**：缺少它时，在 `.on(cb)` 与 `.emit()` 之间一次由 malloc 触发的 GC 会把闭包清扫掉，下一次 emit 就会调用已被释放的内存。如果你的 handle 中存放了闭包指针，请务必注册一个扫描器。"

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:363
msgid "When to extend the perry-ffi surface"
msgstr "何时扩展 perry-ffi 表面"

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:365
msgid ""
"If your binding genuinely needs something perry-ffi doesn't expose, file an "
"issue against [`PerryTS/perry`](https://github.com/PerryTS/perry/issues) "
"describing:"
msgstr "如果你的绑定确实需要 perry-ffi 尚未暴露的能力，请在 [`PerryTS/perry`](https://github.com/PerryTS/perry/issues) 提交 issue，描述："

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:369
msgid "the binding you're writing,"
msgstr "你正在编写的绑定，"

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:370
msgid "the perry-runtime function/type you'd otherwise reach into,"
msgstr "你原本想要直接调用的 perry-runtime 函数 / 类型，"

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:371
msgid "why a higher-level perry-ffi entry would generalize."
msgstr "为什么提供一个更高层的 perry-ffi 入口能够具备通用性。"

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:373
msgid ""
"The bar for adding to perry-ffi is high — every helper is a forever "
"commitment — but real wrappers driving real needs is exactly the right "
"input. The recent additions (BigInt + Buffer in v0.5.556, JSON-stringify + "
"event-pump in v0.5.567 followups) all came from specific wrappers needing "
"them."
msgstr "perry-ffi 添加新条目的门槛很高 —— 每个 helper 都是永久承诺 —— 但由真实需求驱动的真实封装恰恰是最合适的输入来源。最近的几次新增（v0.5.556 中的 BigInt + Buffer，v0.5.567 后续中的 JSON-stringify + 事件泵）都源自具体封装的需要。"

#: src/native-libraries/authoring-guide.md:379
msgid ""
"Don't reach into `perry_runtime::*` directly to \"unblock\" your wrapper "
"today — it'll break the next time those internals change."
msgstr "不要为了“今天就让封装跑通”而直接伸手进 `perry_runtime::*` —— 下一次这些内部实现变化时它就会坏掉。"

