#: src/native-libraries/manifest-v1.md:136
msgid ""
"Note on `\"string\"` vs. `\"i64_str\"`: both produce a string on the "
"TypeScript side, but they differ in how Rust returns the pointer. Use "
"`\"string\"` / `\"ptr\"` when your `extern \"C\" fn` is declared `-> *const "
"u8` (or `*const StringHeader`); use `\"i64_str\"` when it's `-> i64` and the "
"value happens to be a `StringHeader` address (closes [\\#222](https://"
"github.com/PerryTS/perry/issues/222))."
msgstr "关于 `\"string\"` 与 `\"i64_str\"`：在 TypeScript 端两者都会得到一个字符串，但它们在 Rust 侧返回指针的方式不同。当你的 `extern \"C\" fn` 声明为 `-> *const u8`（或 `*const StringHeader`）时使用 `\"string\"` / `\"ptr\"`；当声明为 `-> i64` 而该值恰为 `StringHeader` 地址时使用 `\"i64_str\"`（关闭 [\\#222](https://github.com/PerryTS/perry/issues/222)）。"

