#: src/stdlib/http.md:3
msgid "Perry natively implements HTTP servers, clients, and WebSocket support."
msgstr "Perry 原生实现了 HTTP 服务器、客户端和 WebSocket 支持。"

#: src/stdlib/http.md:5
msgid "Node.js compatibility — `node:http` / `node:https` / `node:http2`"
msgstr "Node.js 兼容性 —— `node:http` / `node:https` / `node:http2`"

#: src/stdlib/http.md:7
msgid ""
"Perry exposes a faithful subset of Node.js's stdlib HTTP server modules on "
"top of hyper + rustls + tokio-tungstenite. The whole shape — handler "
"signature, IncomingMessage / ServerResponse properties + methods, TLS opts, "
"ALPN-negotiated HTTP/2, WebSocket upgrade dispatch — works unmodified, so "
"unmodified Node servers (Express / Koa / Polka / hono via `@hono/node-"
"server` / etc.) compile and run natively (issue #577)."
msgstr "Perry 在 hyper + rustls + tokio-tungstenite 之上忠实地暴露了 Node.js 标准库 HTTP 服务器模块的子集。整体形态——处理函数签名、IncomingMessage / ServerResponse 属性与方法、TLS 选项、ALPN 协商的 HTTP/2、WebSocket 升级派发——都可以原样工作，因此未经修改的 Node 服务器（Express / Koa / Polka / 通过 `@hono/node-server` 的 hono 等）可以原生编译并运行（issue #577）。"

#: src/stdlib/http.md:14
msgid "`http.createServer(handler)`"
msgstr "`http.createServer(handler)`"

#: src/stdlib/http.md:16
msgid ""
"```typescript\n"
"// node:http server (issue #577). Drop-in for Node.js's `http.createServer`\n"
"// — same handler shape `(req, res) => …` and same property/method\n"
"// surface (`req.method`, `req.url`, `req.headers`, `res.statusCode`,\n"
"// `res.setHeader`, `res.end`, `res.write`, `res.writeHead`). The\n"
"// canonical Express body-collection pattern (`req.on('data', ...)`,\n"
"// `req.on('end', ...)`) works against a fully-buffered request body.\n"
"import { createServer } from \"node:http\"\n"
"\n"
"const httpServer = createServer((req: any, res: any) => {\n"
"    if (req.method === \"POST\" && req.url === \"/echo\") {\n"
"        let chunks: string[] = []\n"
"        req.on(\"data\", (chunk: string) => chunks.push(chunk))\n"
"        req.on(\"end\", () => {\n"
"            const body = chunks.join(\"\")\n"
"            res.statusCode = 200\n"
"            res.setHeader(\"Content-Type\", \"text/plain\")\n"
"            res.end(\"got:\" + body)\n"
"        })\n"
"        return\n"
"    }\n"
"    res.statusCode = 200\n"
"    res.setHeader(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n"
"    res.end(`{\"path\":\"${req.url}\"}`)\n"
"})\n"
"\n"
"httpServer.listen(3000, () => {\n"
"    console.log(\"[node:http] listening on http://0.0.0.0:3000\")\n"
"})\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/stdlib/http.md:47
msgid ""
"Supported on `IncomingMessage`: `.method`, `.url`, `.headers`, "
"`.rawHeaders`, `.httpVersion`, `.complete`, `.aborted`, `.destroyed`, "
"`.socket.remoteAddress`, `.socket.remotePort`, `.on('data'|'end'|'close'| "
"'error', cb)`, `.read()`, `.pause()`, `.resume()`, `.destroy()`."
msgstr "`IncomingMessage` 上支持：`.method`、`.url`、`.headers`、`.rawHeaders`、`.httpVersion`、`.complete`、`.aborted`、`.destroyed`、`.socket.remoteAddress`、`.socket.remotePort`、`.on('data'|'end'|'close'| 'error', cb)`、`.read()`、`.pause()`、`.resume()`、`.destroy()`。"

#: src/stdlib/http.md:52
msgid ""
"Supported on `ServerResponse`: `.statusCode` (get/set), `.statusMessage` "
"(set), "
"`.setHeader/.getHeader/.removeHeader/.hasHeader/ .getHeaders/.getHeaderNames`, "
"`.headersSent`, `.writableEnded`, `.writableFinished`, `.writeHead(status, "
"msg?, headers?)`, `.write(chunk)`, `.end(chunk?)`, `.flushHeaders()`, "
"`.on('finish'|'close', cb)`. Auto Content-Length on `.end()` when no "
"`Transfer-Encoding` was set."
msgstr "`ServerResponse` 上支持：`.statusCode`（读/写）、`.statusMessage`（写）、`.setHeader/.getHeader/.removeHeader/.hasHeader/ .getHeaders/.getHeaderNames`、`.headersSent`、`.writableEnded`、`.writableFinished`、`.writeHead(status, msg?, headers?)`、`.write(chunk)`、`.end(chunk?)`、`.flushHeaders()`、`.on('finish'|'close', cb)`。当未设置 `Transfer-Encoding` 时，`.end()` 上会自动写入 Content-Length。"

#: src/stdlib/http.md:60
msgid "`https.createServer({ key, cert }, handler)`"
msgstr "`https.createServer({ key, cert }, handler)`"

#: src/stdlib/http.md:62
msgid ""
"```typescript\n"
"// node:https server (issue #577 Phase 2). Same handler surface as\n"
"// `node:http`, plus a `{ key, cert }` opts arg with PEM-encoded TLS\n"
"// material. rustls 0.23 underneath; the CryptoProvider is installed\n"
"// lazily on first `https.createServer` call. ALPN defaults to\n"
"// `http/1.1`; opt into HTTP/2 by passing\n"
"// `alpnProtocols: [\"h2\", \"http/1.1\"]` (or use `node:http2` directly).\n"
"import { createServer as createTlsServer } from \"node:https\"\n"
"import { readFileSync } from \"node:fs\"\n"
"\n"
"const tlsServer = createTlsServer(\n"
"    {\n"
"        key: readFileSync(\"/tmp/perry-https-cert/key.pem\", \"utf8\"),\n"
"        cert: readFileSync(\"/tmp/perry-https-cert/cert.pem\", \"utf8\"),\n"
"    },\n"
"    (req: any, res: any) => {\n"
"        res.statusCode = 200\n"
"        res.setHeader(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n"
"        res.end(`{\"tls\":\"ok\",\"path\":\"${req.url}\"}`)\n"
"    }\n"
")\n"
"\n"
"tlsServer.listen(443)\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/stdlib/http.md:87
msgid ""
"Both `key` and `cert` are PEM strings (PKCS#8 / RSA / EC keys + multi-cert "
"chains all parse). ALPN defaults to `http/1.1` only — programs that want "
"HTTP/2 should reach for `node:http2`'s `createSecureServer` (which always "
"advertises `[h2, http/1.1]`)."
msgstr "`key` 和 `cert` 都是 PEM 字符串（PKCS#8 / RSA / EC 密钥及多证书链均可解析）。ALPN 默认仅为 `http/1.1`——需要 HTTP/2 的程序应使用 `node:http2` 的 `createSecureServer`（它始终通告 `[h2, http/1.1]`）。"

#: src/stdlib/http.md:92
msgid "`http2.createSecureServer({ key, cert }, handler)`"
msgstr "`http2.createSecureServer({ key, cert }, handler)`"

#: src/stdlib/http.md:94
msgid ""
"```typescript\n"
"// node:http2 server (issue #577 Phase 3). `createSecureServer({ key, "
"cert })`\n"
"// drives a hyper-util auto::Builder so HTTP/2 and HTTP/1.1 share a\n"
"// single port via ALPN auto-negotiation. The handler signature is\n"
"// the same as Phase 1 / Phase 2 — IncomingMessage / ServerResponse\n"
"// are reused as Http2ServerRequest / Http2ServerResponse since each\n"
"// `:path` request becomes a single buffered IncomingMessage.\n"
"import { createSecureServer } from \"node:http2\"\n"
"\n"
"const h2Server = createSecureServer(\n"
"    {\n"
"        key: readFileSync(\"/tmp/perry-https-cert/key.pem\", \"utf8\"),\n"
"        cert: readFileSync(\"/tmp/perry-https-cert/cert.pem\", \"utf8\"),\n"
"    },\n"
"    (req: any, res: any) => {\n"
"        res.statusCode = 200\n"
"        res.setHeader(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n"
"        res.end(`{\"h2\":\"ok\",\"path\":\"${req.url}\",\"httpVersion\":\"$"
"{req.httpVersion}\"}`)\n"
"    }\n"
")\n"
"\n"
"h2Server.listen(8443)\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/stdlib/http.md:118
msgid ""
"Driven through `hyper-util`'s `auto::Builder`, so an HTTP/1.1 client (curl "
"without `--http2`) and an HTTP/2 client (curl with `--http2`) hit the same "
"handler over the same port."
msgstr "通过 `hyper-util` 的 `auto::Builder` 驱动，因此 HTTP/1.1 客户端（不带 `--http2` 的 curl）和 HTTP/2 客户端（带 `--http2` 的 curl）会在同一端口上命中相同的处理函数。"

#: src/stdlib/http.md:122
msgid "WebSocket upgrade — `Server.on('upgrade', (req, wsId, head) => …)`"
msgstr "WebSocket 升级 —— `Server.on('upgrade', (req, wsId, head) => …)`"

#: src/stdlib/http.md:124
msgid ""
"```typescript\n"
"// node:http + WebSocket upgrade (issue #577 Phase 4). The `'upgrade'`\n"
"// event fires once per WebSocket client; the `wsId` argument is\n"
"// already a fully-handshaked, perry-ext-ws-registered connection,\n"
"// so the usual `wsId.on('message', ...)` / `wsId.send(...)` /\n"
"// `wsId.close()` surface works without further plumbing. The\n"
"// IncomingMessage `req` carries the original upgrade request\n"
"// (URL, headers — useful for routing or auth).\n"
"const wsHttpServer = createServer((req: any, res: any) => {\n"
"    res.statusCode = 200\n"
"    res.end(\"perry node:http server with ws upgrade\")\n"
"})\n"
"\n"
"wsHttpServer.on(\"upgrade\", (req: any, wsId: any, _head: any) => {\n"
"    wsId.on(\"message\", (msg: string) => {\n"
"        wsId.send(\"echo:\" + msg)\n"
"    })\n"
"    wsId.send(\"perry-hello\")\n"
"})\n"
"\n"
"wsHttpServer.listen(3001)\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/stdlib/http.md:147
msgid ""
"The HTTP/1.1 server detects `Upgrade: websocket` in the request, performs "
"the handshake server-side (Sec-WebSocket-Accept derived via tungstenite's "
"`derive_accept_key`), then registers the upgraded stream in perry-ext-ws's "
"connection map. The TS-side `wsId` argument is already a fully-connected "
"client — drive it via the standard `wsId.on('message', cb)` / "
"`wsId.send(msg)` / `wsId.close()` surface that standalone "
"`WebSocketServer({ port })` clients use."
msgstr "HTTP/1.1 服务器会检测请求中的 `Upgrade: websocket`，在服务器端完成握手（Sec-WebSocket-Accept 通过 tungstenite 的 `derive_accept_key` 派生），然后将升级后的流注册到 perry-ext-ws 的连接表中。TS 端的 `wsId` 参数已经是一个完整连接的客户端——通过独立 `WebSocketServer({ port })` 客户端使用的标准 `wsId.on('message', cb)` / `wsId.send(msg)` / `wsId.close()` 接口来驱动它。"

#: src/stdlib/http.md:155
msgid "Hono"
msgstr "Hono"

#: src/stdlib/http.md:157
msgid ""
"[Hono](https://hono.dev/) is a runtime-agnostic web framework whose only "
"required interface is `app.fetch(req: Request) → Promise<Response>`. Add it "
"to `perry.compilePackages` and the entire `app.fetch` surface including "
"middleware (`hono/logger`, `hono/cors`, `hono/jwt`), route groups, and JSON "
"responses works unchanged (issues #421, #486, #487 closed). `app.fetch` is "
"enough for testing, edge-runtime deployments (Cloudflare Workers / Vercel "
"Edge / AWS Lambda / Deno Deploy — those runtimes call `app.fetch` "
"themselves), and any scenario where some outer host hands you a `Request`."
msgstr "[Hono](https://hono.dev/) 是一个与运行时无关的 Web 框架，唯一必需的接口是 `app.fetch(req: Request) → Promise<Response>`。将其加入 `perry.compilePackages`，整个 `app.fetch` 接口（包括中间件 `hono/logger`、`hono/cors`、`hono/jwt`、路由分组以及 JSON 响应）即可原样工作（issue #421、#486、#487 已关闭）。`app.fetch` 已足够用于测试、边缘运行时部署（Cloudflare Workers / Vercel Edge / AWS Lambda / Deno Deploy——这些运行时会自行调用 `app.fetch`），以及任何由外部宿主向你传递 `Request` 的场景。"

#: src/stdlib/http.md:167
msgid ""
"```typescript\n"
"import { Hono } from \"hono\"\n"
"import { logger } from \"hono/logger\"\n"
"\n"
"const app = new Hono()\n"
"app.use(\"*\", logger())\n"
"app.get(\"/\", (c) => c.json({ message: \"hello\", ok: true }))\n"
"\n"
"// app.fetch() works end-to-end — feed it a Request, get a Response.\n"
"const res = await app.fetch(new Request(\"http://localhost/\"))\n"
"console.log(res.status, await res.text())\n"
"\n"
"export default app  // for CF Workers / similar runtimes\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

